<h2>Variables</h2>

<p>
    A variable is nothing but a name given to a storage area that our programs can manipulate.<br />
    Each variable in C# has a specific type, which determines the size and layout of the variable's<br />
    memory the range of values that can be stored within that memory and the set of operations that<br />
    can be applied to the variable.
</p>

<p>The basic value types provided in C# can be categorized as:</p>

